<promed@promedmail.org>
[The reported numbers of cases since the last posting on 19 Dec 2004
has increased from 95 to 143, and the number of affected salons has
increased from 18 to 33. Although not stated in the recent outbreak,
the 2001 cluster was primarily due to _Mycobacterium fortuitum_. -
Mod.LL]
